to the editor re increasingly schools move to restrict dodgeball news article may 6 it 's disturbing that educators are only now figuring out the evils of dodgeball we played it in elementary school gym class by sixth grade the boys especially the classroom bullies and future high school football players outweighed the girls by 30 or 40 pounds i clearly remember some girls cowering and turning their backs in an act of concession so that the boys would tag them out gently instead of whapping them with that hard rubber playground ball when it came to humiliation dodgeball was right up there with choosing players for the team when you 'd pray you 'd be picked early and not grouped with the klutzes and outcasts joyce cohen new york may 7 2001

